5.9 #Heavy_Duty_GS_Pulling_Tool is designed to locate in standard internal fishing necks. Based on the standard
GS,the Heavy Duty GS has more dogs for increased bearing area and more robust cores for increased
strength.To engage the GS Pulling/Running Tool,a sit down weight is required fore automatic
engagement.To release the tool,downward jarring activates the release mechanism via the shear pin.

5.10 GU Shear Up Adapter converts the standard sheardown GS Pulling Tool and Heavy Duty GS Pulling
Tool into a shear-up release.To convert the GS Pulling Tools into a shear-up tool,remove the shear
pin and fish neck from the GS Tool and screw on the GU shear up adapter.
Â

5.11 Heavy Duty Shear Up Adapter (as with the GU adapter) is a device used to convert a GS type pulling tool into a GR shear up to release type tool.
However,the heavy duty shear up adapter is designed for applications where it is desirable for the GR to endure some sustained heavy upward jars prior to
releasing,which is not possible with the standard GU adapter.The heavy duty shear up adapter is fitted with a double set of shear pins capable
of sustaining heavy upward jarring before shearing in two stages.In order to achieve the release of the GS pulling tool with the
shear pin removed,heavy duty jarring must be maintained in order to shear out the double set of shear pins.
Â 
Â 
Â 
5.12 Double Jar Down Adapter is designed to add greater flexibility to the GS Pulling tool.The Double Jar Down adapter protects the GS pulling tool shear pin.This
allows the GS Pulling tool to be first jarred downwards without shearing and then upwards to shear a set of pins before ultimately jarring downwards to shear
the GS pulling tool pin.The tool can then be retrieved from the well bore.The double jar down adapter can also be run with the GS pulling tool shear pin removed,effectively
adapting the GS tool into a GR(shear up) tool.

5.23 Heavy Duty Pulling System has been designed to withstand extreme conditions during the retrieval of various downhole devices,especially
'problem fishing situations'where there is damage to internal/external profiles which can impede a successful operation.
The system incorporates a non-releasable 'Anchor' Pulling tool which can be equipped with either a Collet to suit conventional fishing necks,an
Internal Spear to suit various bores or a Grapple Style Overshot for varying external diameters.
The Lower 'Anchor'Tool can be deployed by either the Heavy Duty Pulling Tool or if preferred a standard running tool can be used on the standard fish neck provided.
If a shear up to release running tool is used once latched onto the fish,the running tool should be sheared and returned to surface leaving
the Lower 'Anchor'Tool ready to accept the Heavy Duty Pulling Tool.The Heavy Duty Pulling Tool is then run to dock with the lower non-standard fishing neck on the Lower'Anchor'Tool.
The Lower 'Anchor' Tool features a unique fishing profile designed to integrate with the exclusive Heavy Duty Pulling Tool,to give a clean strong union between neck and pulling tool for optimum
performance.
The Pulling Tool can be parted from the Lower 'Anchor'Tool by jarring down to shear a pin,this functions the Pulling Tool to the release position.The tool will lock at this position,using a springloaded
button,to prevent any unwanted Collet movement,which can complicate release.
Â 
Â 
Â

5.24 Heavy Duty Universal Pulling Tool is designed for running and retrieving down hole flow devices.The tool is based on a collet to give maximum coverage
of the fishing neck and features unique supports between the collet fingers.The supports centralise the fishing neck preventing it hanging on the collet fingers
even in highly deviated conditions.A full sleeve both supports the collet and gives the tool a clean profile.
The heavy duty universal pulling Tool can be adapted from a shear-up to release to a sheardown to release tool,without the need for any
additional parts,it has a universal core which permits the same tool to be able to retrieve devices with fish necks of different lengths or reach(i.e. short,medium or long reach).
